Target: OntoSewage is an ontology developed for representing sewerage system.

Comment: Sewerage component is the infrastructure that conveys sewage or surface runoff (stormwater, meltwater, rainwater) using sewers.
Label: Sewerage component

Comment: Sewage plant is a place where sewage is cleaned so that it is not harmful or dangerous to the environment.
Label: Sewage plant

Comment: Sewerage network is a network of pipes and sewers that work together to collect and drain wastewater from the population or industrial centers to off-site treatment facilities.
Label: Sewerage network

Comment: Sub network is a network that contains branch pipes.
Label: Sub network

Comment: Main network is a network that contains main pipes.
Label: Main network

Comment: Sewerage usage represents what the sewerage is used for.
Label: Sewerage usage

Comment: Pressure drainage is about managing the mix of air and water and maintaining the water seal in the trap, to protect the buildings occupants from foul odours and the risk of bacterial contamination.
Label: Pressure drainage

Comment: Mixed process makes it easier to trap harmful substances by increasing a contact area between a flocculant and an undesirable substance.
Label: Mixed process

Comment: Water that has fallen as or been obtained from rain.
Label: Rain water

Comment: Wastewater is the liquid that comes from showers, washing machines, sinks, toilets, bathtubs, dishwashers, and other items that handle dirty water.
Label: Waste water

Comment: Drainage of street
Label: Street drainage

Comment: A stream, river, lake, ocean, or other surface or groundwaters into which treated or untreated wastewater is discharged.
Label: Pre flood

Comment: A pipe for conveying water.
Label: Water pipe

Comment: Records such as functional state, ID, and owner of a sewerage component.
Label: Sewerage records

Comment: Type of ownership for sewerage component.
Label: Ownership type

Comment: Public ownership means that water could be properly managed at catchment level, and that the whole water cycle could be considered.
Label: Public

Comment: Belongs to the homeowner
Label: Private

Comment: Belongs to the city government
Label: City

Comment: Operational state for sewerage component, i.e., under construction.
Label: Functional state

Comment: Completely built/developed
Label: Constructed

Comment: Regularly available
Label: Stock

Comment: Not available for use
Label: Out of service

Comment: Design or make a plan of (something to be made or built).
Label: Planning

Comment: Protected by interposing material that prevents the transfer of heat between the external environment and fluid circulating through pipes
Label: Insulated

Comment: Construction properties for a sewerage component such as construction year and used materials.
Label: Construction properties

Comment: Concrete is a composite material composed of fine and coarse aggregate bonded together with a fluid cement (cement paste) that hardens over time.
Label: Concrete

Comment: Synthetic polymer of plastic.
Label: Polyvinyl chloride hard

Comment: Concrete in which steel is embedded in such a manner that the two materials act together in resisting forces.
Label: Reinforced concrete

Comment: Stoneware is dense pottery fired at high temperatures to make it resistant to liquids, or non-porous.
Label: Stoneware

Comment: Grey cast iron is a type of cast iron that has a graphitic microstructure.
Label: Gray cast iron

Comment: Type of channel for construction properties
Label: Channel type

Comment: A sluice for controlling or directing the flow of water.
Label: Penstock

Comment: An open pipeline in which the water, according to the law of gravity, travels from a higher starting point to a lower ending point.
Label: Open gravity pipeline

Comment: A closed pipeline in which the water, according to the law of gravity, travels from a higher starting point to a lower ending point.
Label: Closed gravity pipeline

Comment: A surface or shape exposed by making a straight cut through pipe, especially at right angles to an axis.
Label: Cross section

Comment: External form of Manhole's cover, flume, shaft, or cross section.
Label: Shape

Comment: Having the oval shape of an egg.(The depth is one and half times the width.)
Label: Egg shaped

Comment: Open trench means a partially or totally excavated trench, including a trench in which a pipe, conduit or cable has been laid but not fully backfilled to the level of the adjoining ground and finally compacted.
Label: Open trench

Comment: A half of a circle or of its circumference.
Label: Semi circle

Comment: A round plane figure whose boundary (the circumference) consists of points equidistant from a fixed point (the centre).
Label: Circle

Comment: A plane figure with four straight sides and four right angles, especially one with unequal adjacent sides, in contrast to a square.
Label: Rectangle

Comment: A plane figure with four equal straight sides and four right angles.
Label: Square

Comment: Shaped like a circle or cylinder or sphere.
Label: Round

Comment: Having angles or sharp corners.
Label: Angular

Comment: Type of wastewater that is produced by a community of people or natural factors like (rain, flood).
Label: Sewerage fluid

Comment: Water that has fallen as or been obtained from rain
Label: Rain water

Comment: Wastewater produced due to human activities in households is called domestic wastewater i.e. wastewater from the kitchen, shower, wash basin, toilet and laundry.
Label: Domestic waste water

Comment: Type of pipe such as venting.
Label: Pipe type

Comment: Pipe type used for connecting line
Label: Connection line

Comment: Pipe type used for pipe
Label: Pipe

Comment: Pipe type used for connecting duct
Label: Connecting duct

Comment: Pipe type used for relief line
Label: Relief line

Comment: Degree of sloping in pipe.
Label: Inclination

Comment: Connection properties of pipe.
Label: Connection properties

Comment: Type of endpoint which is connected to pipe.
Label: Endpoint type

Comment: The endpoint type used for property connection
Label: Property connection

Comment: The endpoint type used for street inlet where it drains rainwater from the street, sidewalk, square to a sewage system.
Label: Street inlet

Comment: The endpoint type used for manhole connection
Label: Manhole endpoint

Comment: Branch connection means taking a tapping connection from a run pipe directly by making a hole in the run pipe or using an outlet fitting, which provides a connection of pipe for fluid to flow from a higher diameter to a lower diameter of the pipe.
Label: Branch connection

Comment: Type of shaft
Label: Shaft type

Comment: A pipe with an opening which permits escape or release (of liquid, etc).
Label: Outlet

Comment: It is a component of road drainage. It is used to absorb surface water on paved surfaces and feeds it to underground drainage facilities.
Label: Street inlet shaft

Comment: Inspection opening is important point in the sewerage infrastructure and is installed to enable access to underground sewer pipes in the event of a blockage.
Label: Inspection opening

Comment: Type of the connected node to a manhole.
Label: Structure type

Comment: Cover is a removable plate forming the lid over the opening of a manhole, an opening large enough for a person to pass through that is used as an access point for an underground vault or pipe.
Label: Cover

Comment: Type of manhole's cover (It is based on the ability to safely hold up to the relating weight)
Label: Cover class

Comment: Max weight (Domestic driveway thresholds for family cars, vans and 4x4s)
Label: 12.5T

Comment: Max weight (Main roads, highways and high traffic areas such as public car parks)
Label: 40T

Comment: Shaft is below the taper and leads down to the base of the manhole.
Label: Shaft

Comment: Flume is a human-made channel for water, in the form of an open declined gravity chute whose walls are raised above the surrounding terrain.
Label: Flume

Comment: Associated infrastructure of a location.
Label: Associated infrastructure

Comment: A stretch of land, especially with regard to its physical features.
Label: Terrain

Comment: A paved path for pedestrians at the side of a road.
Label: Side walk

Comment: A road that is commonly used and that goes through the main part of a city, town, etc.
Label: Main road

Comment: A minor or subsidiary road, especially one joining or diverging from a main road.
Label: Side road

Comment: Private property refers to the ownership of property by private parties - essentially anyone or anything other than the government.
Label: Private property

Comment: A relationship between a sewerage component and sewerage usage.
Label: has usage

Comment: A relationship between a sewerage component and its records.
Label: has sewerage records

Comment: A relationship between sewerage records and their functional state.
Label: has functional state

Comment: A relationship between sewerage records and their ownership type.
Label: has ownership type

Comment: A relationship between a sewerage component and its construction properties.
Label: has construction properties

Comment: A relationship between construction properties of a sewerage component and their channel type.
Label: has channel type

Comment: A relationship between a pipe and sewerage fluid.
Label: used for

Comment: A relationship between a pipe type and pipe.
Label: has pipe type

Comment: A relationship between a pipe and its cross section.
Label: has cross section

Comment: A relationship between a cross section of a pipe and height.
Label: has height

Comment: A relationship between a cross section of a pipe and width.
Label: has width

Domain: CrossSection UNION Cover UNION Shaft UNION Flume
Comment: A relationship between a cross section of a pipe and shape.
Label: has shape

Domain: http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/Height UNION http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/Width UNION Inclination UNION http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/Length UNION  http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/Thickness UNION http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/Distance UNION http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/Depth

Comment: A relationship between a measure and the respective unit of measure.
A relationship between a pipe and inclination.
Label: has inclination

Comment: A relationship between a pipe or a flume or a shaft and length.
Label: has length

Comment: A relationship between a pipe and its wall thickness.
Label: has wall thickness

Comment: A relationship between a pipe and connection properties.
Label: has connection properties

Comment: A relationship between connection properties of a pipe and endpoint of the connection.
Label: has endpoint type

Comment: A relationship between a branch connection and a pipe.
Label: has branch pipe

Comment: A relationship between a branch connection and a pipe.
Label: has main pipe

Comment: A relationship between a pipe and outlet location.
Label: has outlet location

Comment: A relationship between a pipe and inlet location.
Label: has inlet location

Comment: Distance (in m) between main pipe endpoint and the branch connection on main pipe.
Label: relative distance on main pipe

Comment: A relationship between a manhole and cover.
Label: has cover

Comment: A relationship between a cover and cover class.
Label: has class

Comment: A relationship between a manhole and shaft.
Label: has shaft

Comment: A relationship between a shaft and depth.
Label: has depth

Comment: A relationship between a manhole and flume.
Label: has flume

Comment: A relationship between a shaft and its type.
Label: has shaft type

Comment: A relationship between a manhole and structure type.
Label: has structure type

Comment: A relationship between a location and associated infrastructure.
Label: is associated with

Comment: A relationship between a location and Geo coordinates.
Label: has coordinates

Comment: A relationship between a location and elevation.
Label: has elevation

Comment: A relationship which shows the elevation above see level of a location.
Label: has elevation above sea level

Comment: A relationship between a sewerage component and sewage plant.
Label: is connected to

Comment: A relationship which shows the elevation reference.
Label: has elevation reference

Comment: A relationship which shows the elevation accuracy.
Label: has elevation accuracy

Comment: Sewerage component ID
Label: component ID

Comment: Construction year for sewerage component.
Label: construction year

Comment: Connection ID of pipe
Label: has connection ID

Comment: Source ID of pipe
Label: has source ID

Comment: A relationship to show where the sewage enters a pipe.
Label: has upstream connector

Comment: A relationship to show where the sewage exits a pipe.
Label: has downstream connector

Comment: Endpoint object of pipe
Label: has endpoint object

Comment: Position of branch pipe
Label: clock position of branch pipe

Comment: A relationship to define whether relative distance on main pipe is measured in or against flow direction.
Label: is in flow direction

Comment: A relationship to show whether the location is in water protection zone or not.
Label: is in water protection zone

Comment: A relationship to show whether the location is in flood plane or not.
Label: is in flood plane

Comment: Catchment area key of a location
Label: has catchment area key

Comment: Point designation of a location
Label: has point designation

Comment: District reference of a location
Label: has district reference

Comment: District name of a location
Label: has district name

Comment: Street reference of a location
Label: has street reference

Label: has street name

Label: has position accuracy
